Detailed Description

cvmx_bgx::_spu::_br_pmd_lp_rep

This register implements 802.3 MDIO register 1.153 for 10GBASE-R (when BGX()_CMR()_CONFIG[LMAC_TYPE] = 10G_R) and MDIO registers 1.1200-1.1203 for 40GBASE-R (when BGX()_CMR()_CONFIG[LMAC_TYPE] = 40G_R). It is automatically cleared at the start of training. Each field reflects the contents of the status report field in the associated lane's most recently received training frame. The lane fields in this register are indexed by logical PCS lane ID.

The lane 0 field (LN0_*) is valid for both 10GBASE-R and 40GBASE-R. The remaining fields (LN1_*, LN2_*, LN3_*) are only valid for 40GBASE-R.
